<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2625] auto bootstrapping a node into a cluster without a schema silently fails</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2625</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;from &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mail-archive.com/user@cassandra.apache.org/msg13001.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.mail-archive.com/user@cassandra.apache.org/msg13001.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;StorageService.joinRing() aborts the auto bootstrap process if the cluster does not have a schema defined. It looks like the node is left in the &quot;Joining&quot; mode and there is no logging. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There could be a schema defined and no data loaded, so just having a schema does not make the token selection any better. And BootStrapper.bootstrap() handles their been no non system tables.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can we let the bootstrap process continue ?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
